<doc id="196202" wikidata="Q24221" url="?curid=196202" title="Dresden (region)">
<text>Dresden is one of the three former Direktionsbezirke of Saxony, Germany, located in the east of the state. It coincided with the &quot;Planungsregionen&quot; Oberlausitz-Niederschlesien and Oberes Elbtal/Osterzgebirge.

==History==
The Direktionsbezirk Dresden came into existence on 1 August 2008, and succeeded the Dresden Government Region. It was disbanded in March 2012.

